      {
        "order": 1,
        "text": "In a bowl, combine yogurt, lemon juice, half the garlic, half the ginger, garam masala, cumin, coriander, turmeric, chili powder, salt, and pepper. Add chicken pieces and marinate for at least 30 minutes."
      },
      {
        "order": 2,
        "text": "Rinse basmati rice under cold water until water runs clear. Cook rice in salted boiling water according to package instructions, then drain and keep warm."
      },
      {
        "order": 3,
        "text": "Heat half the butter in a large pan over medium heat. Add chopped onion and sauté until soft and golden."
      },
      {
        "order": 4,
        "text": "Add remaining garlic and ginger, cook for 1 minute until fragrant."
      },
      {
        "order": 5,
        "text": "Add tomato puree and simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally."
      },
      {
        "order": 6,
        "text": "In a separate pan, melt remaining butter and cook marinated chicken over medium heat until browned and cooked through, about 8-10 minutes."
      },
      {
        "order": 7,
        "text": "Add cooked chicken to the tomato sauce, stir well, then pour in heavy cream. Simmer gently for 10 minutes until sauce thickens and chicken is tender."
      },
      {
        "order": 8,
        "text": "Adjust seasoning with salt and pepper. Garnish with fresh coriander."
      },
      {
        "order": 9,
        "text": "Serve butter chicken hot with basmati rice."
